Jamie Carragher has named four players who have joined him in the legendary status of the Liverpool. According to him, Mohamed Salah is already a Liverpool legend even if he leaves the club after 12 months. He noted that the likes of goalkeeper Alisson Becker, defender Virgil Van Dijk and departed Sadio Mane are already Liverpool legends. “How they’ve changed the face of Liverpool Football Club along with the manager means they will all be legends no matter when they move on for the club and for whatever reason they move on from the club,” he told Sky Sports. He said that the Reds fans are happy and thankful for what these players have achieved at the club He also believes that Salah, who signed a new deal with the FA Cup and Carabao Cup holders, will finish his time in the top five or six players ever to have played for the club.